  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">The 40 states of a spin-3/2 particle used by Zimba and Penrose to prove the Kochen–Specker and Bell theorems are shown to be identical (i.e., unitarily equivalent) in <math altimg="si1.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant="double-struck">CP</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup></math> to the 40 rays that follow from the vertices of the Witting polytope. The Witting polytope also gives rise to 120 rays in <math altimg="si2.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant="double-struck">RP</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>7</mn></mrow></msup></math> that give rise to well over a billion parity proofs of the Kochen–Specker theorem. The implications of these results are discussed.</subfield>
    <subfield code="9">Elsevier</subfield>
  </datafield>
